<h3>Cookies and Similar Technologies</h3>

<p>We use "cookies" or similar technologies to collect
information. A cookie is a data file that we store on your phone's storage for
record-keeping purposes. Such "persistent cookies" may include authentication
information for future logins to the application or service. We might also use
"session ID cookies" to better understand how you interact with the app and to
aggregate usage of the app. If you do not accept the use of cookies, you may
not be able to use all or part of the app and its services.</p>

<p>We may also use "clear graphical images", "web beacons" or
other means to collect usage, demographic and geographic data.</p>

<h3>Using social networks</h3>

<p>As a 4<sup>th</sup> & Mayor user who has downloaded,
installed and run the 4<sup>th</sup> & Mayor app software on your Windows
Phone, you can interact with social networking services like foursquare.
Depending on the social network and how you use the connection, you choose to
use the app in accordance with the privacy settings you have set in your social
networking account. You may be able to post information to your social
networking account, including personally identifiable information,? to your
social networking service. For example, you can connect to the foursquare
